Share All sharing options for: How small businesses can get money from the stimulus packageUpdate, April 16: The Paycheck Protection Program (PPP), a new loan initiative aimed at helping small businesses weather the economic fallout from the coronavirus response, has run out of money, according to a statement from the Small Business Administration.
There’s a significant amount of money — $377 billion — allocated to support small businesses in Congress’s latest coronavirus stimulus package.
When small businesses submit their applications for the EIDL loan, they can indicate they are interested in the emergency grant at the same time.
When small businesses submit their applications for the EIDL loan, they can indicate they are interested in the emergency grant at the same time.
PPP TermsThe PPP loans are 100 percent forgivable, depending on whether businesses lay off workers and how they use the money.